name: $title
desc: Returns: The label for this particular section.  This will be part of the rendered content for the document, and is often used to build a table of contents.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The label for this particular section.  This will be part of the rendered content for the document, and is often used to build a table of contents.

name: $code
desc: Returns: A code identifying the kind of content contained within the section. This must be consistent with the section title.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: A code identifying the kind of content contained within the section. This must be consistent with the section title.

name: $text
desc: Returns: A human-readable narrative that contains the attested content of the section, used to represent the content of the resource to a human. The narrative need not encode all the structured data, but is required to contain sufficient detail to make it "clinically safe" for a human to just read the narrative.

name: $mode
desc: Returns: How the entry list was prepared - whether it is a working list that is suitable for being maintained on an ongoing basis, or if it represents a snapshot of a list of items from another source, or whether it is a prepared list where items may be marked as added, modified or deleted.

name: $orderedBy
desc: Returns: Specifies the order applied to the items in the section entries.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Specifies the order applied to the items in the section entries.

name: $entry
desc: Returns: A reference to the actual resource from which the narrative in the section is derived.

name: $emptyReason
desc: Returns: If the section is empty, why the list is empty. An empty section typically has some text explaining the empty reason.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: If the section is empty, why the list is empty. An empty section typically has some text explaining the empty reason.
